42    /**
43    * DateTimeZoneBuilder allows complex DateTimeZones to be constructed. Since
44    * creating a new DateTimeZone this way is a relatively expensive operation,
45    * built zones can be written to a file. Reading back the encoded data is a
46    * quick operation.
47    * <p>
48    * DateTimeZoneBuilder itself is mutable and not thread-safe, but the
49    * DateTimeZone objects that it builds are thread-safe and immutable.
50    * <p>
51    * It is intended that {@link ZoneInfoCompiler} be used to read time zone data
52    * files, indirectly calling DateTimeZoneBuilder. The following complex
53    * example defines the America/Los_Angeles time zone, with all historical
54    * transitions:
55    *
56    * <pre>
57    * DateTimeZone America_Los_Angeles = new DateTimeZoneBuilder()
58    * .addCutover(-2147483648, 'w', 1, 1, 0, false, 0)
59    * .setStandardOffset(-28378000)
60    * .setFixedSavings("LMT", 0)
61    * .addCutover(1883, 'w', 11, 18, 0, false, 43200000)
62    * .setStandardOffset(-28800000)
63    * .addRecurringSavings("PDT", 3600000, 1918, 1919, 'w', 3, -1, 7, false, 7200000)
64    * .addRecurringSavings("PST", 0, 1918, 1919, 'w', 10, -1, 7, false, 7200000)
65    * .addRecurringSavings("PWT", 3600000, 1942, 1942, 'w', 2, 9, 0, false, 7200000)
66    * .addRecurringSavings("PPT", 3600000, 1945, 1945, 'u', 8, 14, 0, false, 82800000)
67    * .addRecurringSavings("PST", 0, 1945, 1945, 'w', 9, 30, 0, false, 7200000)
68    * .addRecurringSavings("PDT", 3600000, 1948, 1948, 'w', 3, 14, 0, false, 7200000)
69    * .addRecurringSavings("PST", 0, 1949, 1949, 'w', 1, 1, 0, false, 7200000)
70    * .addRecurringSavings("PDT", 3600000, 1950, 1966, 'w', 4, -1, 7, false, 7200000)
71    * .addRecurringSavings("PST", 0, 1950, 1961, 'w', 9, -1, 7, false, 7200000)
72    * .addRecurringSavings("PST", 0, 1962, 1966, 'w', 10, -1, 7, false, 7200000)
73    * .addRecurringSavings("PST", 0, 1967, 2147483647, 'w', 10, -1, 7, false, 7200000)
74    * .addRecurringSavings("PDT", 3600000, 1967, 1973, 'w', 4, -1, 7, false, 7200000)
75    * .addRecurringSavings("PDT", 3600000, 1974, 1974, 'w', 1, 6, 0, false, 7200000)
76    * .addRecurringSavings("PDT", 3600000, 1975, 1975, 'w', 2, 23, 0, false, 7200000)
77    * .addRecurringSavings("PDT", 3600000, 1976, 1986, 'w', 4, -1, 7, false, 7200000)
78    * .addRecurringSavings("PDT", 3600000, 1987, 2147483647, 'w', 4, 1, 7, true, 7200000)
79    * .toDateTimeZone("America/Los_Angeles", true);
80    * </pre>
81    *
82    * @author Brian S O'Neill
83    * @see ZoneInfoCompiler
84    * @see ZoneInfoProvider
85    * @since 1.0
86    */
